23/02/2004
CONSTANTA, Romania -- Justice Minister Rodica Stanoiu said Saturday (21 February) that ongoing judicial reforms are going smoothly. 
She stressed that the legislative and institutional adjustments are on schedule and well in line with the EU accession strategy, despite recent EU criticism about judicial reform.
In other news, Romanian Defence Minister Ioan Mircea Pascu visited Sarajevo on Sunday and pledged support for the defence reforms underway in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH). 
He said BiH, like most countries in the region, is headed in the right direction. 
(Rompres, Nine o'Clock, Dnevni avaz - 23/02/04; Onasa, BBC - 22/02/04)
